                                        <depth unit="cm">3</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.damaged"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Four lines of Greek text, somewhat compressed and uneven lines with a consistent left margin.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.incomplete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Cleanly v-cut letters, lunate in form but somewhat irregular in size, without serifs. Alpha has straight bar and slight apex; epsilon is lunate; zeta is plain Z; kappa has full length arms; mu has vertical first and last, with middle strokes only descending halfway; rho has small curved but open loop; sigma is lunate; omega is large and lunate.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line3">Line 1-3</locus>
