                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name type="nomen">Ῥῶσκι</name> <name type="cognomen">Μά
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>γνε</name></persName> χρησ
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>τὲ χαῖρε
                    <lb n="4"/>ἔζησες ἔ
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">τη</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text from autopsy</note></app>
                    <app loc="4"><note>Orsi: ἔζησε σ[εμνῶς]</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Roscius Magnus, a good man, farewell. You lived [--] years...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The parallel offered by <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004364">ISic004364</ref> and <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004365">ISic004365</ref> suggests that <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔζησες ἔ[τη]</foreign> is more plausible as a restoration in lines 4-5 than Orsi's proposal of  <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔζησε σ[εμνῶς]</foreign>.</p>
            </div>
